Type: Package
Package: ClinicoPath
Title: Comprehensive Analysis for Clinicopathological Research
Version: 0.0.33.10
Date: 2026-02-09
Authors@R: person(given = "Serdar", family = "Balci", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "serdarbalci@serdarbalci.com", comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7852-3851"))
Maintainer: Serdar Balci <serdarbalci@serdarbalci.com>
Description: ClinicoPath is a comprehensive jamovi module designed specifically 
    for clinicopathological research and medical data analysis. It provides an 
    integrated suite of statistical tools, visualization methods, and reporting 
    functions tailored for pathology, clinical research, and medical decision-making. 
    The package organizes analysis tools into five main functional areas: 
    ClinicoPath Descriptives (Table One generation, cross-tabulation, data quality 
    assessment), ClinicoPath Survival (Kaplan-Meier curves, Cox regression, 
    competing risks), Medical Decision Analysis (ROC curves, diagnostic tests, 
    decision curves), Statistical Plots (publication-ready visualizations), and 
    Specialized Visualizations (waterfall plots, alluvial diagrams, forest plots). 
    Key features include integration with jamovi's user-friendly interface, 
    clinical terminology familiar to researchers, reproducible research capabilities, 
    and advanced statistical methods including bootstrap confidence intervals and 
    effect size calculations. The package serves as an umbrella coordinating 
    multiple specialized sub-modules and can be used through jamovi's GUI or 
    directly in R for programmatic analysis.
